<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>zf create controller  creates a controller with first letter capitalized no matter whether we supply a mixed-case name or not.</p>

<p>The same does not happen in zf create module .</p>

<p>This is a problem because if someone made a module like zf create module admin, it creates the module with the name admin (in the xml profile)</p>

<p>and then when someone tries to create a model, zf create model test -m admin, it creates a model with class name admin_Model_Test and not Admin_Model_Test</p>

